        @Since(value="7.0")
public VolumePair(Long clusterPairID,
                Long remoteVolumeID,
                Long remoteSliceID,
                String remoteVolumeName,
                UUID volumePairUUID,
                RemoteReplication remoteReplication)
        The Volume Pair Info is an object containing information about a volume that is paired on a remote cluster. If the volume is not paired, this object is null.
        Parameters:
        clusterPairID - [required] The remote cluster a volume is paired with.
        remoteVolumeID - [required] The VolumeID on the remote cluster a volume is paired with.
        remoteSliceID - [required] The SliceID on the remote cluster a volume is paired with.
        remoteVolumeName - [required] The last-observed name of the volume on the remote cluster a volume is paired with.
        volumePairUUID - [required] A UUID in canonical form.
        remoteReplication - [required] Details about the replication configuration for this volume pair.
        Since:
        7.0
